On Wednesday we examined perceptions of ethos statements made by
fashion choices, including a specific class comparison of those made
by Beyonce and Taylor Swift. Later we went over the details of our
group project and the stakeholder analysis part.
\begin{enumerate}
\item {\bfseries\sffamily OOPS} Read EAA chs. 16 \& 17
\label{sec:orgf9c8dab}
\item Project 1, Stakeholder Analysis
\label{sec:org006a87e}
\begin{itemize}
\item Every team will generate a list of major stakeholders within the
controversy that your group is studying
\item Within your team, each group member will select one stakeholder that
they will become an expert on, irrespective of your own position on
the issue
\item Each person will:
\begin{itemize}
\item Write a 6-page (1800 words) rhetorical analysis of one
stakeholder's position, argument, and rhetorical strategies
\item Cite at least one source made by the stakeholder
\item These analyses should strive to provide a fair analysis of your
stakeholder's position by quoting from and closely engage with
source \emph{produced} by those stakeholders.
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Focus/Purpose/genre
\label{sec:orge0d5cdb}
Makes an argument about the stakeholder's use of rhetoric (not about
the issue itself). Clearly identifies a stakeholder and offers
effective analysis of the stakeholder's position and arguments.
\end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}
