What audience will you focus on? List two or three. What venue would
you imagine it being published in? (Newspaper, blog, website, etc.)
Be specific. Is there a particular angle or feature of the debate
you'd like to address?

I would not change my argument for different audiences, rather, I
would change the way that I communicate this argument so as to be
understood best by those who read.

I may focus not on the listeners and participants of the IDW, but the
critics of the IDW. On a website or online media site perhaps. I would
likely address the fundamentals of the IDW, and what they really seem
to be. Whether or not I agree with them, just stating them and the
things that these speakers are trying to achieve in getting together.
