Format for Op-ed Submission: "Turner op-ed \#1"
\textbf{Heuristic} - "a tool that helps you make up things"
\emph{Learning how to learn} (Soccer guy, "Chiche")
\begin{enumerate}
\item {\bfseries\sffamily DONE} EAA Ch. 14 \& 15 and "Document Design"
\label{sec:org72ec5b3}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Document Design
\label{sec:org9c8877e}
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Document Design} = visual appearance (not content)
\item \textbf{Unity} = repetition and consistency. 
"Do all elements in my document work together visually?"
\item \textbf{Variety} = varied, topic specific design choices
\item \textbf{Balance} = harmony/equilibrum/proportionality
\item \textbf{Emphasis} = drawing attention to important parts
\item \textbf{Layout} = spatial arrangement
\item \textbf{White Space} = easier to read
\item ACADEMIC vs. BUSINESS WRITING ?
\item \textbf{Typeface} = a general font (Verdana, Courier)
\item \textbf{Font} = a specific font (Century \textbf{bold}, Verdana \emph{italics}, etc.)
\item \textbf{Visuals}
\begin{itemize}
\item make simple and uncluttered
\item only when necessary
\item label/number tables and figures
\item balance b/w figs and text
\item give credit if not your own
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\item EAA 14
\label{sec:orgf3fa0c4}
\item EAA 15
\label{sec:orgef77ae4}
\begin{itemize}
\item Formal Presentations: \textbf{Purpose}, \textbf{Audience}, \textbf{Structure}
\item Strong introductions and conclusions
\item Clear structures and signposts
\item Straightforward syntax and concrete diction
\item Repetition, parallelism, and climactic order
\item \textbf{Oral} presentations: practice, time, and record
\item Websites, Blogs, Wikis, Videos
\end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}
